# Clawdbot — Cursor Rules

## Code Standards — BINDING (from CLAUDE.md)

- Maximum file size: 300 lines (JS/TS) / 500 lines (Python). Split before adding.
- TypeScript for all new and touched files. Rename .js → .ts when refactoring. Use tsx. Strict, no any.
- No silent failures. Every catch: (a) handles with recovery, (b) logs with context, or (c) has // intentional: reason.
- Zero process.env outside config.js/config.ts. All env access through config module.
- Classes for stateful services. Manual DI via constructor params. No DI container.
- Single entrypoint per feature. Dispatch over if/else chains.
- No magic numbers or strings. Constants in constants.ts or config.ts.
- Concurrent operations where independent (Promise.all). Never await sequentially.
- Unit tests for all new code (node:test + esmock).
- EVO X2 is the primary host. Bot runs on EVO. Pi is backup + dashboard screen only.
- Deploy: git push, then ssh james@100.90.66.54 'cd ~/clawdbot && git pull && npm install && sudo systemctl restart clawdbot'.

---

## READ FIRST
Read `CLAUDE.md` and `architecture.md` for full system context.

## Cursor agent — SSH and timeouts (mandatory)

- **Same machine as Claude Code:** This workspace has the SSH key at `C:\Users\James\.ssh\id_ed25519` and normal LAN access. **Do not assume SSH is blocked** or that deploy “can’t work from the sandbox” — run the commands and use real exit output.
- **Run `ssh` / `scp` directly** in the integrated terminal (one command per invocation is fine). Prefer the **copy-paste blocks below** over PowerShell wrapper scripts unless you are batching many files in one script the user asked for.
- **`cargo build --release`** on the Pi typically takes **~1m45s** and can run longer. When using a tool with a wait budget, allow **at least 5 minutes (300000 ms)** for that step, **or split deploy:** finish SCP + `systemctl restart` first, then run **only** `ssh ... "source ~/.cargo/env; cd ~/clawd-dashboard && cargo build --release"` in a **separate** command with a long timeout.
- If a combined pipeline times out, **split into separate terminal steps** (Node deploy → dashboard SCP → cargo build → relaunch → EVO hop) instead of giving up.

## SSH Key
All SSH/SCP commands use: `-i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519`

## Targets

| Target | Host | User | Path |
|--------|------|------|------|
| Pi (bot backend) | `192.168.1.211` | `pi` | `~/clawdbot/` |
| Pi (dashboard) | `192.168.1.211` | `pi` | `~/clawd-dashboard/` |
| EVO X2 (voice + memory API) | via Pi hop | `james` | `~/clawdbot-memory/` |

## Deploy Node.js (bot backend) to Pi

```bash
# 1. Copy changed file(s)
scp -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 src/<file>.js pi@192.168.1.211:~/clawdbot/src/<file>.js

# 2. Restart service
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "sudo systemctl restart clawdbot"

# 3. Verify
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "journalctl -u clawdbot --no-pager -n 10"
```

For files in subdirectories:
```bash
scp -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 src/tools/handler.js pi@192.168.1.211:~/clawdbot/src/tools/handler.js
```

## Deploy Dashboard (Rust) to Pi

```bash
# 1. Copy source (include api.rs if changed)
scp -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 clawd-dashboard/src/main.rs clawd-dashboard/src/api.rs pi@192.168.1.211:~/clawd-dashboard/src/

# 2. Build on Pi — allow ~2–5+ minutes; run as its own command if your runner has a short default timeout
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "source ~/.cargo/env; cd ~/clawd-dashboard && cargo build --release"

# 3. Relaunch
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "pkill clawd-dashboard 2>/dev/null; sleep 2; export XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000 WAYLAND_DISPLAY=wayland-0; nohup /home/pi/clawd-dashboard/target/release/clawd-dashboard > /tmp/clawd-dashboard.log 2>&1 &"

# 4. Verify
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "sleep 2 && tail -5 /tmp/clawd-dashboard.log"
```

## Deploy Memory Service (FastAPI on EVO) — includes `POST /route-command`

Voice routing calls `http://localhost:5100/route-command` on EVO; code lives in `memory-service/`.

```bash
# 1. Stage on Pi
scp -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 memory-service/main.py memory-service/command_router.py pi@192.168.1.211:/tmp/

# 2. Pi → EVO (same tree as voice_listener)
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "scp /tmp/main.py /tmp/command_router.py james@192.168.1.230:~/clawdbot-memory/"

# 3. Restart memory API (unit name from voice service: After=clawdbot-memory.service)
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "ssh james@192.168.1.230 'sudo systemctl restart clawdbot-memory'"

# 4. Verify
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "ssh james@192.168.1.230 'curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" -X POST http://127.0.0.1:5100/route-command -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"text\\\":\\\"show calendar\\\"}\"'"
```

## Deploy Voice Listener to EVO X2 (via Pi hop)

The EVO X2 is not directly reachable from this machine. SSH hop through Pi.

```bash
# 1. Copy to Pi as staging
scp -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 evo-voice/voice_listener.py pi@192.168.1.211:/tmp/voice_listener.py

# 2. Pi copies to EVO
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "scp /tmp/voice_listener.py james@192.168.1.230:~/clawdbot-memory/voice_listener.py"

# 3. Restart voice service on EVO
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "ssh james@192.168.1.230 'sudo systemctl restart clawdbot-voice'"

# 4. Verify
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "ssh james@192.168.1.230 'journalctl -u clawdbot-voice -n 10 --no-pager'"
```

## Deploy EVO systemd services (rare)

```bash
# Copy service file to Pi, then to EVO
scp -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 evo-voice/clawdbot-voice.service pi@192.168.1.211:/tmp/clawdbot-voice.service
ssh -i C:/Users/James/.ssh/id_ed25519 pi@192.168.1.211 "scp /tmp/clawdbot-voice.service james@192.168.1.230:/tmp/ && ssh james@192.168.1.230 'sudo cp /tmp/clawdbot-voice.service /etc/systemd/system/ && sudo systemctl daemon-reload && sudo systemctl restart clawdbot-voice'"
```

